history.text: I thought this movie was really cute and funny - a bit different than other animations out there.
I thought the references to species-ism in it were interesting.
I remember Idris Elba and Jason Bateman were perfect for their roles.

Yeah, it's nice that Disney always includes subject matter/concepts for adults, rather than have everything be directed toward kids that may watch it. I found the array of animals quite interesting, I would say most people don't even know what a African Buffalo is.
Jason Bateman did an awesome job - his laid back demeanor fit the fox character well!
I'd forgotten Hopps was the academy valedictorian.
She was definitely a perfectionist!
That's good though, as the plot would have go nowhere had she not been so clever/stubborn.
Indeed. She showed that on parking duty, in fact!
I really related to that bit - stuck in a job you hate, lol!
Did it come out around Christmas? I see it being called a holiday treat, but I didn't see it until it was Netflix... :D
I saw it in theaters, I think it came out around March.
Oh the carrot pen, that was cute!
I've forgotten that too. Maybe I should watch it again.
Never thought an Otter would be all the scary, but holy crap seeing that rabid Mr. Otterton was like whoa!
I definitely wouldn't be opposed to rewatching it. Maybe movie night with my daughter.
That I do recall. Otters are the epitome of cute when you see them typically... then that.
It would be a great movie to watch on Family night. I've definitely watched it more than once!
I remember the predator-prey tension thing.
I felt back about Nick's background, but it wasn't anything that couldn't be guessed at. Characters like that usually have a SOB story that makes them jerks later on.
But I forgot Hopps quit.
Ah yes, predator prey. Did you think Nick would attack Judy at the end?
Yeah, that species-ism at work. I don't know.
That would have made for an R-rated children's movie, lol!
Ah yes, Bellwether as the mastermind. It's coming back to me.
I thought the Nighthowlers looked a lot like the Crocuses in my yard that were coming up around the same time the movie came out - just a random thought I'd throw out there.
Haha, the blueberries!
Ah that darn sheep - what a baaaaaitch!
Haha, baaaaitch. Well said!
It's the quiet ones you have to watch out for!
did you like the music from the movie?
Shakira and all.
I don't remember a thing about the music.
Oh, there was that big production where she was an animal performing wasn't there?
I thought that aspect of it was amusing.
I remember the one song when Judy is first entering Zootopia - "Try Anything" or something like that. Super catchy. Yes, that Leopard secretary kept playing with the music video app!
98% on rotten tomatoes, not surprising! Disney movies usually do pretty well.
Yeah, the lower IMDB rating not surprising either.
Well, it was lovely "talking" with you!
Actually, that's probably about what I would give it... 8 or so.
yeah me too
Heh, you too.
bye!

uid2response.feedback: My partner touched on a thing or two that wasn't mentioned in the document... Interesting task though. I'd forgotten a lot of the movie -- might watch it again now soon since I've been reminded of some high points.
